  <h2>The Usual Suspects</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Baffles.</strong> They keep solids where they belong; when they deteriorate, solids can escape toward the field.</li>
    <li><strong>Effluent pumps.</strong> Systems that pump uphill rely on a pump that can fail.</li>
    <li><strong>Pipes and lines.</strong> Crushed or root-invaded lines restrict flow.</li>
    <li><strong>Distribution boxes.</strong> A small box that unbalances the whole field — see <a href="/septic-distribution-box-problems/">distribution-box problems</a>.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Evaluation Comes First</h2>
  <p>
    Similar symptoms can come from different components, so a provider evaluates before recommending a repair. To get started, <a href="/request-service/">request septic service</a> and describe what you are seeing.
  </p>

